This paper is likely to belong to the category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL) as it deals with the representation of polysemous words and linguistic analysis of multi-sense word embeddings. It could also belong to "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) as it proposes a novel method for dimensionality reduction. Additionally, it could be categorized under "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) as it deals with natural language processing and representation learning. It could also be classified under "Information Retrieval" (cs.IR) as word embeddings are often used in information retrieval tasks. Finally, it could belong to "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE) as neural network-based methods are commonly used for word embedding generation.
